Below is a worked‐through example of how one can replicate the two grouped structures exactly as shown, using only the orientations provided in the “Block Dictionary” images.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1)  ANALYSIS OF MAIN TARGET IMAGE
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
•  Left “House‐Like” Structure  
   –  Total of 8 blocks in 2 “layers.”  
   –  Bottom/First Layer (7 blocks):  
       1) Three vertical orange cylinders in the center.  
       2) One tall green rectangular prism on each side of the cylinders.  
       3) One orange wedge on each outer flank, sloping inward.  
   –  Top/Second Layer (1 block):  
       1) One orange wedge forming a “roof” centered above the cylinders.

•  Right “Arch” Structure  
   –  Total of 5 blocks in 3 “layers.”  
   –  Bottom Layer (2 cubes): one green cube on the left, one blue cube on the right.  
   –  Middle Layer (2 matching red quarter‐circle blocks) creating a half‐circle “cut‐out.”  
   –  Top Layer (1 green rectangular block) spanning the full width of the arch.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2)  SELECTING/INDEXING THE NECESSARY DICTIONARY BLOCKS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Below are the dictionary indices (and colors/orientations) that match each piece **without** any re‐orientation:

•  Left “House‐Like” Structure (8 blocks)
  1.  Green rectangular prism (tall) – Dictionary #5  × 2  
  2.  Orange cylinder (vertical) – Dictionary #7       × 3  
  3.  Orange wedge (sloping left‐to‐right) – #12       × 1 (left side)  
  4.  Orange wedge (mirror slope) – #16                × 1 (right side)  
  5.  Orange wedge (roof orientation) – #14            × 1  

•  Right “Arch” Structure (5 blocks)
  1.  Green cube – Dictionary #3                       × 1  
  2.  Blue cube – Dictionary #2                        × 1  
  3.  Red quarter‐circle block – #1                    × 2  
  4.  Green rectangular block (horizontal) – #4         × 1  

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3)  STEP‐BY‐STEP ASSEMBLY INSTRUCTIONS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
{  
  Step1:  Move block with index 5   (left tall green pillar)  
  Step2:  Move block with index 5   (right tall green pillar)  
  Step3:  Move block with index 7   (1st orange cylinder)  
  Step4:  Move block with index 7   (2nd orange cylinder)  
  Step5:  Move block with index 7   (3rd orange cylinder)  
  Step6:  Move block with index 12  (left orange wedge at base)  
  Step7:  Move block with index 16  (right orange wedge at base)  
  Step8:  Move block with index 14  (orange wedge “roof”)  

  Step9:  Move block with index 3   (green cube, bottom left of arch)  
  Step10: Move block with index 2   (blue cube, bottom right of arch)  
  Step11: Move block with index 1   (red quarter‐circle, middle left)  
  Step12: Move block with index 1   (red quarter‐circle, middle right)  
  Step13: Move block with index 4   (green rectangular block on top)  
}

Following the above sequence and using the indicated dictionary blocks in their exact orientations will reproduce the target arrangement as shown in the reference image.
